Some 121 road constructors in Nandi County have been ordered to defer work for the next two weeks following heavy rains in the region. Governor Stephen Sang suspended all ongoing road construction and maintenance works across the county until May 17 when the heavy rains are expected to subside. ALSO READ:

Six-year-old girl buried alive in West Pokot landslides Sang has also suspended the ongoing grading of 1,080 kilometres of county roads; and the gravelling of 300 kilometres being conducted by the county Roads Department. “Heavy rains have posed a heavy challenge to ongoing road maintenance works,” said the governor. The county was recently declared a disaster zone after heavy rains wreaked havoc, destroying private and public utilities and causing mudslides and landslides.